name: Canadian North 737-275(A) Combi [C-GOPW] Takeoff from Edmonton Airport ᴴᴰ
description:
Canadian North is an airline based in Northern Canada, operating primarily 737s on milk runs from Yellowknife and Iqaluit to a number of northern towns. Their fleet consists mostly of 737-300s now, but they still operate two classic 737-200s equipped with gravel kits for flights into unpaved airports. This particular one is 37 years old, and first flew with Pacific Western Airlines, was then transferred to Canadian Airlines after the two merged, and then to Air Canada when it and Canadian merged. It now flies with Canadian North, Canadian Airlines' former northern division, hence the "Empress" callsign, which was Canadian's former callsign. Anyway, enjoy this classic 737 departing Edmonton for Yellowknife, with ATC.

Thanks for watching!
